@everyone
Hello everyone, I have an announcement to make. This might come as a big shock to you, especially for those who have been here for a long time, but I've decided to step down as the owner of RPurgatory, and leave the server. Now **please** don't panic about this, because I'm not doing this over stress, or drama, or over some sort of breakdown.. I'm doing this because I want to take time away from here to work, and grow other servers I've yet to put major time on as of late. To be honest, I've lost my motivation to work on and roleplay on Rpurg for a long time now, but I want to use the motivation I do have on the servers I've been motivated to work on. It's **no one's** fault that I feel this was about Rpurg as a whole, it's just how I personally feel. But don't get me wrong, I love this place and still do, and I will cherish the memories we made on here! But now, it's time for me to move on, to things that might become even bigger than RPurgatory one day.. But this doesn't mean I won't have any interest for RPurg to grow like this too.
As of now, Seth will become the new owner of RPurgatory, and I hope you all welcome my decision with open arms. I trust that RPurg will be a good hands, and so should you.
Don't worry, I'll still come back to check on the server every so often, and you're all free to speak to me whenever you want! And if you ask nicely, I might tell you about the things I've been working on, too! But for now, goodbye. And I can't wait to see all the new developments RPurgatory as a whole might have in the future!
Farewell to all of you, and have a nice day!
- Bee

Hey all, I'm sure many have noticed Tupperbox having semi-frequent periods of dropped or slow proxies recently. They usually last 1-5 minutes and then resolve without intervention. 

The root cause of these "laggy" periods is Discord erroring out on many proxy-related requests. I contacted them about it and they said it's a recurring issue and they're working on making these error windows smaller but it's a complicated issue to fix. 

There isn't much we can do on our end to help Discord so we'll just have to ride out these periods of higher error rates until they can improve the situation. In the meantime please be patient and simply retry proxies if they fail (you can do this by editing or resending the proxy if it doesn't go through). Thanks for your patience!

Hey, I'm aware of some lag issues when using Tupperbox right now. I don't see anything sketchy in the resource monitors or logs but I issued a rolling restart to the bot anyway. I messed it up a little so your cluster will be down for up to five minutes before coming back up instead of one minute, so when the bot stops responding in your server please just hold on until it comes back. With some luck it should improve the lag. Thanks!

**New updates!**
`tul!nick` - Nicknames!
   - This command allows you to set nicknames for your tuppers.
   - Nicknames are currently global but server-bound nicknames (like Discord does them) are planned.
   - This allows you to have a tupper with a complex name which is still easy to refer to in commands (keep the name simple but set the nickname to fancy text, emojis, etc).
   - This allows you to have multiple tuppers with the same displayed name.
`tul!private` - Basic privacy settings!
   - This command allows you to set your tupper list to be private or not.
   - Public lists can be queried by anyone, even across servers. Private lists cannot be queried this way.
   - Even if your list is private, proxying with a tupper will expose it and your proxy can be queried to find your Discord user.
   - This command is scoped. Please see `tul!help private` for a description of scopes.
   - More granular privacy settings are planned.
`tul!purge` - Purge your user data.
   - This command nukes all user-associated data (tuppers, groups, configs) for your account from the database. Requires confirmation.
   - If there's any chance you'll still want your data later, be sure to take an export with `tul!export` first.

Other stuff:
   - Proxied message replies now quote the message being replied to, similar to old Discord replies.
   - If a message was deleted by a moderation bot or other proxy bot before Tupperbox got to it, Tupperbox removes the proxy too.
   - Improved responses from several commands to highlight what the bot thinks you were trying to input
   - Fixed `tul!remove` requiring quotes to remove a single tupper with spaces in its name. Now quotes are optional when removing one tupper.
   - Fixed an exploit sometimes allowing tuppers to ping roles the user couldn't normally ping.
   - Fixed some bugs related to using variants of "<text>" as brackets

We welcome your feedback in the support server! #deleted-channel

messages.content:
**New updates!**
`tul!edit` - Edit sent proxies!
   - This command allows you to edit messages you've sent using your tuppers.
   - The recommended way to use it is to **reply to the proxy you wish to edit** while running the command. Write the new message you want to say after the command, like `tul!edit hello there!`.
   - You can also supply a message ID or a message link before the new message to target a message that way. Message links work in DMs too.
   - You can also react to a sent proxy with 📝 to have Tupperbox prompt you for the edited content in DMs.
   - Edited proxies will be logged if a logging channel is configured (check `tul!cfg log`).

Other stuff:
   - `tul!showuser` has been improved. You can now use it while replying to a proxy to query that proxy, or provide a message link or ID like with `tul!edit` to query a message that way.
   - `tul!stats` now shows REST and gateway latencies.

Please let us know in the support server if you have any suggestions (#deleted-channel) or find a bug (#deleted-channel)!

EDIT:
We're aware that both methods of editing a proxy via DM are broken. I'm working on a fix now, might have it out today but more likely it will be fixed tomorrow. I'll send out another update when it's fixed.

EDIT:
You can now use `tul!edit` with a message link in DMs. 📝 reacting is disabled temporarily as a more involved fix needs to be implemented due to cluster shenanigans. An announcement will be made tomorrow when it's fixed.

**New updates!**
`tul!show` - Show off profile cards for your tuppers!
   - This command brings up a nifty display of a single tupper's basic information. You can use it to quickly view a tupper's brackets or birthday or something else without trudging through `tul!list`.
`tul!cfg` - New permissions system! Role-based restrictions!
   - `tul!cfg` now has some new subcommands to replace `tul!cfg blacklist` and `tul!cfg cmdblacklist`.
   - Now you modify channel permissions like this: `tul!cfg allow proxies #channel` or `tul!cfg deny commands #channel`
   - You can now supply a **role ping** instead of a channel to allow/deny permissions for certain roles.
   - Don't specify any channel or role to affect the "default permissions" instead (like the at-everyone role).
   - A new permission has been added: `queries`! By denying this permission to a role or channel, users will be unable to use "query functions" like tul!find, tul!showuser, and  reactions. This allows for channels with more privacy or denying certain people the ability to snoop on other users' tuppers.
   - Use `tul!cfg show` to view a quick summary of the server's permissions.
   - `tul!cfg blacklist` and `tul!cfg cmdblacklist` are deprecated and now refer you to the new system.

Other stuff:
   - Spruced up the help menu with some nifty categories! It should be easier to pick through now.
   - Fixed some broken responses here and there.
   - Error message for when people try to proxy in DMs
   - Tupper limits have been tightened to 500 for most users - exceptions are made for people who are already above the new limit.

**Bugfixes!**
- Avatar restrictions have been re-tested and completely lifted as Discord seems to be accepting any images.
- The default avatar for tuppers is now to have *no* avatar rather than the usual imgur question mark.
- `tul!list` no longer says "No group" under every tupper when the user has no groups.
- Tuppers and groups with emoji names should now work properly all the time instead of sometimes not being able to reference them with commands. 
- Brackets checking has been fixed so two tuppers can no longer be made to have the same brackets.
- `tul!brackets` now no longer occasionally mangles the brackets when the tupper name is a substring of `brackets`
- Multiple tuppers can no longer be activated by one line when the brackets of some tuppers are contained in the brackets of another (e.g. `aaatext` and `atext`) - instead the tupper with the most specific brackets is chosen
- Activating multiple tuppers with one message by using one tupper on each line now also proxies the lines that weren't activating a tupper, meaning tupperbox no longer eats some text sometimes
- Replies & attachments no longer duplicate for each proxy in a multiproxy message, instead the reply is attached to the first proxy and the attachment is sent with the last one

Please report to the support server if you notice any new bugs with these fixes!
pog

A couple of notable fixes:
- Fixed a bug causing custom emoji (and other discord text objects) to not work as brackets. Now you can use custom & animated emoji in your brackets!
- Fixed a bug causing channel permissions in some older servers to be applied as server-wide permissions. This should fix some issues with proxies or commands not working in some servers.

Hey y'all, Tupperbox seems to be having some network issues - lots of shards are timing out and getting kicked offline. I'm gonna give it a full restart to see if that helps things since work seems to be piling up and that's probably not good.

Tupperbox is restarting now, it will come back up in your server within ~30 minutes.

Just for general awareness, Discord seems to have rolled out a change to slash commands on some platforms that is causing issues when trying to use some tuppers.

On some updated clients, any tuppers whose brackets start with a slash (like `/text` or `/hi text`) will no longer be usable: when you try to proxy with them, Discord thinks you're trying to use a slash command and "shakes" the client to reject the message. The exact behavior depends on your platform - it is unknown what platforms will get this change, but at the moment at least Windows seems to be affected.

There's unfortunately nothing we can do about this since it's something Discord built into the app, so if you're encountering issues, you'll probably have to simply change the brackets for those tuppers to keep using them. Going forward it's probably going to be best to avoid use of slashes in your brackets in general. Let us know in the support server if you have any questions!

Edit: Putting a space before the slash stopped working, so the only option is to change the brackets.

__**Check out the new Tupperbox Community Server!**__

Tupperbox has always found success because it provided a useful tool for remarkably under-served communities, like plural servers & roleplay servers. It's thanks to you guys spreading the word that Tupperbox is as big as it is today! We'd like to give back to all of you that made Tupperbox successful, so we've decided to use this platform and set up an official Community Server in order to bring people together and offer a central point for these many disparate groups to meet and find new friends and servers - as well as potentially offer further support or events in the future!

**The Community Server has three sections:**
 Roleplay Category
       - Join roleplays or share your favorite interactions in other rps!
 Plural Category
       - Meet other plural folk or learn about plurality!
 Tabletop Category
       - Discuss popular tabletop systems like DnD!

If you're interested in meeting new people, joining some roleplays, finding new servers in any of these three categories, or just hanging out with other Tupperbox users in general, come take a look! *The community server is advertising-friendly within designated channels!*

https://discord.gg/CMYt4rgvkG 

**Amplify your server with a Server Sponsorship!**
The community server has a designated Sponsored Servers channel in each section, where anyone can go to find new places to hang out, roleplay, meet plural friends, etc.
Want to request sponsorship for your server? Join the server and shoot one of our staff a DM!

*If you're only interested in strictly bot-related updates, don't worry - this will be the only announcement like this.*

Small progress report as it's been two months since thread support was deployed and reverted:

In a nutshell, the thread support problems came from third-party code we were relying on. Two months ago, we decided to rewrite all of that third-party code. We're using the opportunity to include lots of other improvements and refactors to the code. We're confident that these reworks and rewrites will be more than worth it; we're expecting serious benefits to stability and rolling out new features going forward, especially support for new Discord features. This won't impact any existing data or features, and by the end we should have thread support fully functioning again.

We've been working hard and our current goal is to roll out these new rewrites by **October 18th**. I'll write up a blog post after that with more technical details about the rewrites.

If you have any questions or concerns feel free to let us know in the support server. Thanks for your patience and support!

messages.content:
**Tupper Avatars Disappearing**
We've gotten a lot of reports over the past couple days about missing avatars for tuppers.  If you notice some of your tupper avatars are missing, try checking your `tul!list` or `tul!show "tupper name"` for the Avatar URL.  If you click the link and get a strange XML "Access Denied" error, this means Discord has deleted the image from their storage. Unfortunately, Tupperbox has no control over whether Discord continues to store images, so if this happens you'll need to reupload the avatar.


*Why Now?*
Apparently Discord continued storing some images even after the server they were uploaded in got deleted, but now they seem to be going back to some large old deleted servers and deleting those images.  The result is that some avatars that worked fine for a long time are now getting deleted and no longer working.

This is consistent with the warning given by Tupperbox whenever you set an avatar with an image attachment:
> Note: if the message you just used to upload the avatar with gets deleted, the avatar will eventually no longer appear.


To avoid avatar issues like these in the future, we suggest the following best practices:
Set avatars in Tupperbox's DMs or private servers, where the messages are less likely to be deleted.
When possible, keep backups of your tupper avatars on your device, as it can be very difficult to find the originals if Discord deletes them.
Consider uploading avatars to an external host like Imgur and using the direct URL instead of using Discord attachments to protect against Discord deletions. Tupperbox does this automatically for Premium users!


Let us know in the support server if you have any concerns or questions! <https://discord.gg/rHxMbt2>
